day for night ( french : la nuit &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) is a 1973 french film directed by françois truffaut . it stars jacqueline bisset and jean-pierre léaud . it is named after the filmmaking process referred to in french as la nuit &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ( " american night " ) , whereby sequences filmed outdoors in daylight are shot using film stock balanced for tungsten ( indoor ) light and &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ( or adjusted during post production ) to appear as if they are taking place at night . in english , the technique is called day for night , and is the film 's english title .